<!-- ============================== MAIN CONTENT ============================== -->
<main class="main">

<!-- ───── OVERVIEW ───── -->
<section id="overview">
    <h1>RS Medallion <span class="version">v1.0 · dbt 1.9 · Snowflake</span></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
        A production-grade <span class="highlight">Medallion Architecture</span> built with dbt Core on Snowflake —
        featuring custom SCD Type 2 engines, hash-based change detection, automated audit capture, and a comprehensive
        test framework spanning Bronze → Silver → Gold layers.
    </p>

    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header"><span class="icon">📦</span><h4>Tech Stack</h4></div>
        <table class="tbl">
            <tr><td class="mono">dbt-core</td><td>1.9.4</td><td>Transformation framework</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">dbt-snowflake</td><td>1.9.2</td><td>Snowflake adapter</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">dbt_utils</td><td>1.3.3</td><td>Utility macros</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">dbt_external_tables</td><td>0.12.0</td><td>External table support</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">logging</td><td>0.8.0</td><td>Audit logging base package</td></tr>
        </table>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ───── ARCHITECTURE ───── -->
<section id="architecture">
    <h2>🏛️ Architecture Overview</h2>
    <p>The RS Medallion project implements a four-layer data architecture with a cross-cutting audit layer.
       Each layer has a specific purpose, materialization strategy, and dedicated Snowflake database.</p>

    <div class="arch-diagram">
        <div class="arch-layer l-source">
            <h4>📥 Source (Staging)</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                Databases: <code>WORKDAY.STAGING</code> · <code>EQAI.STAGING</code><br>
                External tables loaded via Snowpipe / external ingestion. Raw, unprocessed data.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-layer l-bronze">
            <h4>🥉 Bronze — Operational Data Store (ODS)</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                Databases: <code>WORKDAY.ODS</code> · <code>EQAI.ODS</code><br>
                Materialization: <strong>Incremental</strong> with MERGE · Deduplication · Hash-based CDC · Soft deletes
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-layer l-silver">
            <h4>🥈 Silver — Common Data Model (CDM)</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                Database: <code>CDM.WORKFORCE</code><br>
                Materialization: <strong>Incremental</strong> · Multi-source enrichment · Business-friendly naming · SCD Type 1
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-layer l-gold">
            <h4>🥇 Gold — Core Presentation</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                Database: <code>CORE.SHARED_DIMS</code> · <code>CORE.WORKFORCE</code><br>
                Materialization: <strong>SCD Incremental (Type 2)</strong> for Dims · <strong>Table</strong> for Facts
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-layer l-audit">
            <h4>🔍 Audit — Cross-Cutting Observability</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                Database: <code>AUDIT.DATA_TRANSFORMATION</code><br>
                Run results · DML counts · Query IDs · Audit logging · 60-day retention
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ───── PROJECT STRUCTURE ───── -->
<section id="project-structure">
    <h2>📁 Project Structure</h2>
    <div class="code-block">
<pre><code class="file-tree"><span class="dir">RS_Medallion/</span>
├── <span class="file">dbt_project.yml</span>          ← Project config, layer database routing
├── <span class="file">packages.yml</span>             ← dbt package dependencies
│
├── <span class="dir">models/</span>
│   ├── <span class="dir">0_audit/</span>              ← Audit layer: run results schema
│   │   ├── <span class="file">DBT_RUN_RESULTS.sql</span>
│   │   └── <span class="file">audit_schema.yml</span>
│   │
│   ├── <span class="dir">1_bronze/</span>             ← ODS layer: source-aligned incremental models
│   │   ├── <span class="dir">es_eqai/</span>          ← ES EQAI Users source
│   │   │   ├── <span class="file">ODS_ES_EQAI_USERS.sql</span>
│   │   │   ├── <span class="file">ODS_ES_EQAI_USERS.yml</span>
│   │   │   └── <span class="file">z_es_equai_sources.yml</span>
│   │   └── <span class="dir">workday/</span>          ← Workday HRIS source
│   │       ├── <span class="file">ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE.sql</span>
│   │       ├── <span class="file">ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE.yml</span>
│   │       └── <span class="file">z_workday_sources.yml</span>
│   │
│   ├── <span class="dir">2_silver/</span>             ← CDM layer: business-modeled entities
│   │   └── <span class="dir">cdm/workforce/</span>
│   │       ├── <span class="file">EMPLOYEE.sql</span>
│   │       └── <span class="file">EMPLOYEE.yml</span>
│   │
│   └── <span class="dir">3_gold/</span>               ← Core layer: presentation-ready dims &amp; facts
│       └── <span class="dir">core/</span>
│           ├── <span class="dir">shared_dims/</span>  ← SCD Type 2 dimensions
│           │   ├── <span class="file">DIM_EMPLOYEE.sql</span>
│           │   └── <span class="file">DIM_EMPLOYEE.yml</span>
│           └── <span class="dir">workforce/</span>    ← Transactional facts
│               ├── <span class="file">FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE.sql</span>
│               └── <span class="file">FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE.yml</span>
│
├── <span class="dir">macros/</span>
│   ├── <span class="dir">audit/</span>                ← Audit logging, run result capture, schema routing
│   ├── <span class="dir">helpers/</span>              ← Hash generation, surrogate keys, trimming
│   ├── <span class="dir">purge/</span>               ← Staging dedup, soft delete marking
│   ├── <span class="dir">scd_engines/</span>          ← Custom SCD Type 2 materialization engine
│   └── <span class="dir">utils/</span>               ← Database/schema introspection
│
└── <span class="dir">tests/</span>
    ├── <span class="dir">automation/</span>           ← LLM-based test generation prompt &amp; scripts
    ├── <span class="dir">generic/</span>              ← 17+ reusable parametric test macros
    └── <span class="dir">singular/</span>             ← Model-specific test files per layer</code></pre>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ───── DATA FLOW ───── -->
<section id="data-flow">
    <h2>🔄 Data Flow Pipeline</h2>
    <p>Each <code>dbt build</code> invocation walks through the following pipeline, with tests running after each model:</p>

    <div class="flow">
        <div class="flow-node node-source">STG Tables<br><small>Snowpipe</small></div>
        <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
        <div class="flow-node node-bronze">ODS Bronze<br><small>Incremental + MERGE</small></div>
        <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
        <div class="flow-node node-silver">CDM Silver<br><small>Incremental + Enrich</small></div>
        <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
        <div class="flow-node node-gold">Core Gold<br><small>SCD2 Dim + Fact</small></div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout callout-info">
        <strong>💡 Build Command</strong>
        Use <code>dbt build --select +FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE</code> to build all upstream models and run all associated tests in dependency order.
    </div>

    <h3>Pipeline Steps</h3>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body"><strong>on-run-start Hook:</strong> Creates the audit log table (<code>AUDIT.DATA_TRANSFORMATION.dbt_audit_log</code>) if it doesn't exist.</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Bronze Layer:</strong> <code>ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE</code> and <code>ODS_ES_EQAI_USERS</code> load incrementally from staging with pre-hook duplicate purging and post-hook soft-delete marking.</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Bronze Tests:</strong> 17 tests per ODS model — PK uniqueness, not-null, email format, row count reconciliation, PK reconciliation.</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Silver Layer:</strong> <code>EMPLOYEE</code> CDM model enriches Workday data with ES EQAI user IDs via LEFT JOIN, applies business naming and type casting.</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">5</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Silver Tests:</strong> 13 tests — referential integrity to ODS, PK/row count reconciliation, business rule validation.</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">6</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Gold Dimension:</strong> <code>DIM_EMPLOYEE</code> uses the custom <code>scd_incremental</code> materialization with <code>scd+merge</code> strategy to maintain SCD Type 2 history.</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">7</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Gold Fact:</strong> <code>FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE</code> is a full-refresh table that derives lifecycle events (HIRE, TERM, LOA, RETURN, ROLE_CHANGE, ORG_TRANSFER, PROFILE_UPDATE) from SCD2 version diffs.</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">8</div><div class="step-body"><strong>on-run-end Hook:</strong> Captures all run results to <code>AUDIT.DATA_TRANSFORMATION.dbt_run_results</code> with DML counts via <code>RESULT_SCAN</code>.</div></div>
</section>

<hr>

<!-- ═══════════════════════ LAYER DEEP DIVES ═══════════════════════ -->

<!-- ───── BRONZE ───── -->
<section id="bronze">
    <h2>🥉 Bronze Layer — Operational Data Store (ODS)</h2>
    <p>The Bronze layer ingests raw staging data into the ODS with minimal transformation. Its primary goals are:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Deduplication</strong> — Removes duplicate records from staging using <code>ROW_NUMBER()</code> windowing</li>
        <li><strong>Type Casting</strong> — Standardizes column data types with explicit <code>CAST</code></li>
        <li><strong>Audit Metadata</strong> — Adds batch IDs, timestamps, operation types, and data quality placeholders</li>
        <li><strong>Hash-Based CDC</strong> — Generates <code>HASH_CHANGE</code> and <code>HASH_FULL</code> for downstream change detection</li>
        <li><strong>Soft Deletes</strong> — Post-hook marks records no longer in staging as deleted</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Model Configuration</h3>
<pre><code>{{
    config(
        materialized='incremental',
        unique_key='ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE_PK',
        merge_no_update_columns = ['ODS_INS_BATCH_ID', 'ODS_INSERT_TIMESTAMP'],
        merge_condition="DBT_INTERNAL_SOURCE.HASH_CHANGE != DBT_INTERNAL_DEST.HASH_CHANGE",
        tags=["bronze","ods","workday","data-observe"],
        pre_hook  = ["{{ purge_staging_duplicates_by_hash(...) }}"],
        post_hook = ["{{ mark_deleted_records(...) }}"]
    )
}}</code></pre>

    <h3>Key Design Patterns</h3>
    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Implementation</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Surrogate Key</td><td><code>generate_surrogate_key([trim_string('EMPLOYEE_ID')])</code> → MD5 hash PK</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Incremental Filter</td><td><code>WHERE STG_INSERT_TIMESTAMP >= get_max_event_time('STG_INSERT_TIMESTAMP')</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Deduplication</td><td><code>ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY pk ORDER BY timestamp DESC) = 1</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Merge Condition</td><td>Only updates when <code>HASH_CHANGE</code> differs (skip no-op merges)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Immutable Columns</td><td><code>merge_no_update_columns</code> protects insert batch/timestamp</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Pre-Hook</td><td><code>purge_staging_duplicates_by_hash</code> removes true duplicates from staging</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Post-Hook</td><td><code>mark_deleted_records</code> soft-deletes records missing from latest staging batch</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>CTE Structure</h3>
    <div class="callout callout-tip">
        <strong>🧩 Standard CTE Pattern (all Bronze models)</strong>
        <code>CTE_source_data</code> → <code>CTE_source_data_deduped</code> → <code>CTE_audits</code> → <code>CTE_transformed</code> → Final SELECT with hash columns
    </div>

    <h3>Database Routing</h3>
    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Staging Table</th><th>ODS Target</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">Workday</td><td class="mono">WORKDAY.STAGING.STG_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE</td><td class="mono">WORKDAY.ODS.ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">ES EQAI</td><td class="mono">EQAI.STAGING.STG_ES_EQAI_USERS</td><td class="mono">EQAI.ODS.ODS_ES_EQAI_USERS</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</section>

<!-- ───── SILVER ───── -->
<section id="silver">
    <h2>🥈 Silver Layer — Common Data Model (CDM)</h2>
    <p>The Silver layer transforms ODS data into business-modeled entities with clean naming, cross-source enrichment, and standardized field structures. This is where <strong>SCD Type 1</strong> (overwrite) semantics apply — each record represents the <em>current state</em> of an entity.</p>

    <h3>EMPLOYEE CDM Model</h3>
    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Aspect</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Source</td><td><code>ref('ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE')</code> enriched with <code>ref('ODS_ES_EQAI_USERS')</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Target</td><td><code>CDM.WORKFORCE.EMPLOYEE</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Materialization</td><td>Incremental with hash-based merge condition</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Unique Key</td><td><code>CDM_EMPLOYEE_PK</code> (MD5 hash of EMPLOYEE_ID)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SCD Type</td><td><strong>Type 1</strong> — latest value overwrites previous</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Multi-Source Enrichment Pattern</h3>
    <p>The EMPLOYEE model demonstrates a sophisticated re-enrichment pattern:</p>

<pre><code>-- Regular incremental records from Workday ODS
CTE_source_data → filters by ODS_UPDATE_TIMESTAMP

-- Reprocess records where ES_USER_ID was previously NULL
CTE_reprocess_null_es_users → finds employees needing re-enrichment

-- Combine both sets
CTE_combined_source → UNION ALL of new + reprocess records

-- Enrich with ES EQAI user data
CTE_source_enriched → LEFT JOIN to ODS_ES_EQAI_USERS on user_code</code></pre>

    <div class="callout callout-success">
        <strong>✅ Re-Enrichment Logic</strong>
        On incremental runs, the model re-processes existing CDM records where <code>ES_USER_ID IS NULL</code> and a matching ES EQAI record now exists. This ensures eventually-consistent enrichment even when source systems load asynchronously.
    </div>

    <h3>Transformations Applied</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Column Renaming:</strong> <code>LEGAL_NAME_FIRST_NAME</code> → <code>FIRST_NAME</code>, <code>EMAIL_ID</code> → <code>EMAIL_ADDRESS</code></li>
        <li><strong>Derived Fields:</strong> <code>COMPLETE_NAME</code> via <code>CONCAT_WS</code>, <code>IS_UNION_MEMBER</code> from <code>UNION_CODE</code></li>
        <li><strong>Type Conversions:</strong> Boolean <code>IS_DELETED</code> (Y/N → 1/0)</li>
        <li><strong>Data Lineage:</strong> <code>SOURCE_TABLES</code> dynamically includes ES EQAI when join matches</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<!-- ───── GOLD ───── -->
<section id="gold">
    <h2>🥇 Gold Layer — Core Presentation</h2>
    <p>The Gold layer provides consumption-ready dimensional models. It contains two sub-patterns:</p>

    <h3>DIM_EMPLOYEE — SCD Type 2 Dimension</h3>
    <p>Uses the custom <code>scd_incremental</code> materialization with <code>scd+merge</code> strategy. This is the heart of the framework's Type 2 SCD implementation.</p>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Aspect</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Materialization</td><td><code>scd_incremental</code> (custom Snowflake materialization)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Strategy</td><td><code>scd+merge</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Business Key</td><td><code>EMPLOYEE_EIN</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Surrogate Key</td><td><code>EMPLOYEE_SK</code> = MD5(EMPLOYEE_EIN || EFF_DT)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Hash Column</td><td><code>DBT_HASH</code> (from CDM <code>HASH_FULL</code>) drives change detection</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SCD Fields</td><td><code>EFF_DT</code>, <code>DISC_DT</code>, <code>IS_CURRENT</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Batch Tracking</td><td><code>INS_BATCH_ID</code>, <code>UPD_BATCH_ID</code> (YYYYMMDDHHMMSS format)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>SCD Type 2 Merge Logic</h3>
    <p>The custom merge executes three operations in a single statement:</p>

    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong>WHEN MATCHED (Intra-Day Update):</strong> If the source record's batch date matches the target's <code>EFF_DT</code> (same day) AND hashes differ → UPDATE the current record in-place (avoids creating redundant versions for same-day changes).
    </div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong>WHEN NOT MATCHED (New Employee):</strong> If the business key doesn't exist at all → INSERT with <code>EFF_DT = '1900-01-01'</code> (initial load sentinel).
    </div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong>WHEN NOT MATCHED (New Version):</strong> If the hash doesn't match any open record → INSERT new version with current <code>EFF_DT</code>.
    </div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-body">
        <strong>Close-Out UPDATE:</strong> Separate UPDATE sets <code>DISC_DT = CURRENT_DATE - 1</code> and <code>IS_CURRENT = FALSE</code> on old records where hash changed and <code>DISC_DT = '9999-12-31'</code>.
    </div></div>

    <div class="callout callout-warn">
        <strong>⚠️ Post-Hook: Soft Delete Propagation</strong>
        A post-hook UPDATE propagates <code>IS_DELETED = TRUE</code> from the CDM source to all matching DIM records, ensuring delete events are tracked in the dimension.
    </div>

    <h3>FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE — Transactional Fact</h3>
    <p>A <strong>full-refresh table</strong> that derives lifecycle events by comparing consecutive SCD2 versions using <code>LAG()</code> window functions.</p>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Event Type</th><th>Detection Logic</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">HIRE</td><td>First version (<code>VERSION_NUM = 1</code>)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">TERMINATION</td><td>Status changed to TERM/T from non-TERM</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">LOA</td><td>Status changed to LOA</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">RETURN</td><td>Previous status was LOA, now active</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">ORG_TRANSFER</td><td><code>DIV_SK != PREV_DIVISION_NUMBER</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">ROLE_CHANGE</td><td><code>JOB_CD != PREV_JOB_CODE</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">PROFILE_UPDATE</td><td>Catch-all for other changes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>Additional computed measures per event:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Tenure:</strong> <code>TENURE_DAYS</code>, <code>TENURE_MONTHS</code>, <code>TENURE_YEARS</code>, <code>TENURE_BAND</code></li>
        <li><strong>Change Tracking:</strong> <code>IS_PROMOTION</code>, <code>IS_LATERAL</code>, <code>IS_DIVISION_CHANGE</code>, <code>IS_TERMINATION</code></li>
        <li><strong>Fiscal Calendar:</strong> <code>EVENT_FISCAL_YEAR</code>, <code>EVENT_QUARTER</code>, <code>EVENT_MONTH</code></li>
    </ul>
</section>

<!-- ───── AUDIT ───── -->
<section id="audit-layer">
    <h2>🔍 Audit Layer — Observability</h2>
    <p>The audit layer provides complete observability over every dbt run. It consists of two mechanisms:</p>

    <h3>1. dbt Audit Log</h3>
    <p>Created via the <code>on-run-start</code> hook. Records model start/end events, invocation IDs, and query IDs to <code>AUDIT.DATA_TRANSFORMATION.dbt_audit_log</code>.</p>

    <h3>2. dbt Run Results (<code>capture_run_results</code>)</h3>
    <p>The <code>on-run-end</code> hook captures comprehensive execution metadata for every node:</p>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">model_execution_id</td><td>Unique ID: <code>invocation_id.unique_id</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">query_id</td><td>Snowflake query ID for each execution</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">rows_inserted/updated/deleted</td><td>Extracted via <code>RESULT_SCAN</code> on the query_id</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">execution_time</td><td>Duration in seconds</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">compiled_code</td><td>Full compiled SQL (up to 16MB)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">status</td><td>success, error, warn, skipped</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">materialization</td><td>Configured materialization type</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="callout callout-info">
        <strong>📊 Elementary Compatibility</strong>
        The <code>dbt_run_results</code> schema is aligned with the open-source Elementary data observability package, enabling compatibility with Elementary's monitoring dashboards without additional configuration.
    </div>

    <h4>Data Retention</h4>
    <p>Audit records older than <strong>60 days</strong> are automatically purged on each run via:</p>
<pre><code>DELETE FROM AUDIT.DATA_TRANSFORMATION.dbt_run_results
WHERE created_at < DATEADD(day, -60, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP());</code></pre>
</section>

<hr>

<!-- ═══════════════════════ CORE CONCEPTS ═══════════════════════ -->

<section id="scd">
    <h2>🔀 SCD Type 1 vs Type 2</h2>
    <p>This project implements both SCD patterns at different layers:</p>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Aspect</th><th>Type 1 (Silver CDM)</th><th>Type 2 (Gold Dimension)</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>History</td><td>❌ No history — latest value overwrites</td><td>✅ Full history with versioning</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Model</td><td><code>EMPLOYEE</code></td><td><code>DIM_EMPLOYEE</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Materialization</td><td><code>incremental</code> (standard)</td><td><code>scd_incremental</code> (custom)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Strategy</td><td><code>merge</code></td><td><code>scd+merge</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Change Detection</td><td><code>HASH_CHANGE</code> in merge condition</td><td><code>DBT_HASH</code> comparison in SCD merge</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Temporal Fields</td><td>None</td><td><code>EFF_DT</code>, <code>DISC_DT</code>, <code>IS_CURRENT</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Key Structure</td><td>Natural key PK (<code>CDM_EMPLOYEE_PK</code>)</td><td>Surrogate SK (<code>EMPLOYEE_SK</code> = hash of EIN + EFF_DT)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Use Case</td><td>Current-state reporting, operational queries</td><td>Historical analysis, as-of-date reporting</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</section>

<section id="materializations">
    <h2>⚙️ Materializations</h2>
    <p>The project uses four materialization types:</p>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Layer</th><th>Model(s)</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">incremental</td><td><span class="layer-tag tag-bronze">Bronze</span> <span class="layer-tag tag-silver">Silver</span></td><td>ODS_*, EMPLOYEE</td><td>Standard dbt merge with hash-based change detection</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">scd_incremental</td><td><span class="layer-tag tag-gold">Gold</span></td><td>DIM_EMPLOYEE</td><td>Custom materialization for SCD Type 2 with 3-way merge</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">table</td><td><span class="layer-tag tag-gold">Gold</span></td><td>FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE</td><td>Full refresh on every run</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">incremental</td><td><span class="layer-tag tag-audit">Audit</span></td><td>DBT_RUN_RESULTS</td><td>Append-only audit records</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Custom <code>scd_incremental</code> Materialization</h3>
    <p>Defined in <code>macros/scd_engines/snowflake_merge.sql</code>, this custom materialization:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Validates the incremental strategy (<code>merge</code>, <code>delete+insert</code>, or <code>scd+merge</code>)</li>
        <li>Creates a temp relation with the new/changed source data</li>
        <li>Expands target column types if needed</li>
        <li>Dispatches to <code>get_scd_merge_sql</code> for the three-phase merge + close-out</li>
        <li>Runs post-hooks (soft-delete propagation) within the transaction</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section id="incremental">
    <h2>📈 Incremental Strategy</h2>
    <p>All incremental models follow a consistent watermark pattern:</p>

<pre><code>{% if is_incremental() %}
    WHERE timestamp_col >= '{{ get_max_event_time("timestamp_col") }}'
{% endif %}</code></pre>

    <h3><code>get_max_event_time</code> Macro</h3>
    <p>This macro queries the target table for the maximum value of a timestamp column, then subtracts <strong>3 minutes</strong> as a safety buffer to handle late-arriving records:</p>

<pre><code>SELECT max({{ date_field }}) - interval '3 minutes' FROM {{ this }};</code></pre>

    <div class="callout callout-warn">
        <strong>⚠️ Fallback</strong>
        If the result is <code>NULL</code> (empty table), the macro returns <code>'19000101000000000'</code> to process all records.
    </div>

    <h3>Custom <code>is_incremental()</code> Override</h3>
    <p>The project overrides dbt's built-in <code>is_incremental()</code> to add support for a <code>load_historical</code> config flag that forces incremental mode even when the target relation doesn't exist yet — useful for backfill scenarios.</p>
</section>

<section id="hash-change">
    <h2>#️⃣ Hash-Based Change Detection</h2>
    <p>Two hash columns are generated for every Bronze and Silver model:</p>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Hash</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Excludes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">HASH_CHANGE</td><td>Detects business data changes (used in merge conditions)</td><td>Natural keys, audit columns, <code>*_PK</code> columns</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">HASH_FULL</td><td>Full record fingerprint (used as <code>DBT_HASH</code> in SCD2)</td><td>Only audit columns</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>How It Works</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Reads column metadata from the model's YAML file</li>
        <li>Identifies columns tagged with <code>meta.natural_key: true</code> or <code>meta.audit_column: true</code></li>
        <li>Auto-excludes columns ending in <code>_PK</code></li>
        <li>Concatenates remaining columns: <code>coalesce(cast(col as varchar), '') || '|' || ...</code></li>
        <li>Returns <code>MD5(concatenated_string)</code> as a 32-character hash</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout callout-tip">
        <strong>🏷️ YAML Metadata Tags</strong>
        To exclude a column from <code>HASH_CHANGE</code>, add <code>meta: { natural_key: true }</code> or <code>meta: { audit_column: true }</code> in your model's YAML file.
    </div>
</section>

<hr>

<!-- ═══════════════════════ MACROS ═══════════════════════ -->

<section id="macro-overview">
    <h2>🧩 Macro Overview</h2>
    <p>The project contains 16+ custom macros organized into four categories:</p>

    <div class="arch-diagram">
        <div class="arch-layer l-audit">
            <h4>macros/audit/ — Audit &amp; Logging</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                <code>audit.sql</code> · <code>capture_run_results.sql</code> · <code>generate_schema_name.sql</code> · <code>get_audit_location.sql</code>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-layer l-silver">
            <h4>macros/helpers/ — Data Transformation Helpers</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                <code>generate_hash_change.sql</code> · <code>generate_hash_full.sql</code> · <code>generate_surrogate_key.sql</code> · <code>get_max_event_time.sql</code> · <code>trim_string.sql</code> · <code>get_last_query_id.sql</code>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-layer l-bronze">
            <h4>macros/purge/ — Data Cleanup</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                <code>purge_staging_duplicates_by_hash.sql</code> · <code>mark_deleted_records.sql</code>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-layer l-gold">
            <h4>macros/scd_engines/ — SCD Materialization Engine</h4>
            <div class="meta">
                <code>snowflake_merge.sql</code> · <code>merge.sql</code> · <code>insert.sql</code> · <code>is_incremental.sql</code>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="scd-engine">
    <h2>🔧 SCD Merge Engine</h2>
    <p>The SCD engine is the most complex custom component. It defines a new Snowflake materialization (<code>scd_incremental</code>) and merge strategy.</p>

    <h3>Materialization Flow</h3>
<pre><code>{% materialization scd_incremental, adapter='snowflake' %}
  1. Read config: unique_key, timestamp_column, type6_columns
  2. Check existing_relation
  3. If new table → CREATE TABLE AS
  4. If existing → CREATE TEMP TABLE, then dispatch scd+merge
  5. Run post-hooks within transaction
  6. COMMIT
{% endmaterialization %}</code></pre>

    <h3>Merge SQL (3-Phase)</h3>
    <h4>Phase 1: MERGE Statement</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>WHEN MATCHED</strong> (intra-day): UPDATE current record if same-day batch and hash changed</li>
        <li><strong>WHEN NOT MATCHED</strong> (new key): INSERT with <code>EFF_DT = '1900-01-01'</code></li>
        <li><strong>WHEN NOT MATCHED</strong> (new version): INSERT new version row</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Phase 2: Close-Out UPDATE</h4>
<pre><code>UPDATE target
SET DISC_DT = CURRENT_DATE - 1, IS_CURRENT = FALSE
WHERE unique_key = source.unique_key
  AND DBT_HASH &lt;&gt; source.DBT_HASH
  AND DISC_DT = '9999-12-31';</code></pre>

    <h4>Phase 3: Type 6 Hybrid (Optional)</h4>
    <p>If <code>type6_columns</code> are configured, changed column values from the current record are propagated to <em>all historical records</em> — enabling Type 6 (hybrid) SCD behavior.</p>
</section>

<section id="helper-macros">
    <h2>🛠️ Helper Macros</h2>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Macro</th><th>Usage</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td class="mono">generate_surrogate_key</td>
                <td><code>{{ generate_surrogate_key(['COL_A', 'COL_B']) }}</code></td>
                <td>Creates MD5 hash from concatenated, null-safe field values with <code>'-'</code> separator</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="mono">generate_hash_change</td>
                <td><code>{{ generate_hash_change(relation=this) }}</code></td>
                <td>MD5 hash of non-key, non-audit columns for business change detection</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="mono">generate_hash_full</td>
                <td><code>{{ generate_hash_full(relation=this) }}</code></td>
                <td>MD5 hash of all non-audit columns for full record fingerprinting</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="mono">get_max_event_time</td>
                <td><code>{{ get_max_event_time('TIMESTAMP_COL') }}</code></td>
                <td>Returns max timestamp - 3 minutes from target for incremental watermark</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="mono">trim_string</td>
                <td><code>{{ trim_string('FIELD_NAME') }}</code></td>
                <td>LTRIM + RTRIM + REGEXP_REPLACE for multi-space normalization</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="mono">get_last_query_id</td>
                <td><code>{{ get_last_query_id() }}</code></td>
                <td>Queries Snowflake <code>INFORMATION_SCHEMA.QUERY_HISTORY</code> for dbt's last execution query ID</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</section>

<section id="purge-macros">
    <h2>🧹 Purge &amp; Cleanup Macros</h2>

    <h3><code>purge_staging_duplicates_by_hash</code></h3>
    <p>Runs as a <strong>pre-hook</strong> on Bronze models. Removes true duplicate rows from staging tables using a hash-based dedup strategy:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Computes an MD5 hash over all non-excluded columns</li>
        <li>Uses <code>RANK()</code> to identify duplicates (same hash)</li>
        <li>Deletes rows where <code>rank > 1</code>, keeping only the latest per hash</li>
    </ol>
    <p><strong>Excluded columns:</strong> <code>STG_INSERT_TIMESTAMP</code>, <code>EXEC_BATCH_ID</code>, <code>SOURCE_SYSTEM</code>, <code>*_PK</code></p>

    <h3><code>mark_deleted_records</code></h3>
    <p>Runs as a <strong>post-hook</strong> on Bronze models. Performs soft-delete detection:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Compares ODS records against the latest staging batch</li>
        <li>Records not found in staging are marked: <code>OPERATION_TYPE = 'DELETE'</code>, <code>SRC_DEL_IND = 'Y'</code></li>
        <li>Supports both single-column and composite primary keys</li>
        <li>Intelligently trims string PKs and skips numeric PKs</li>
        <li>Includes first-run guard — safely skips if ODS table doesn't exist yet</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section id="audit-macros">
    <h2>📋 Audit &amp; Logging Macros</h2>

    <h3>Lifecycle Hooks</h3>
    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Hook</th><th>Macro</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">on-run-start</td><td><code>create_audit_log_table()</code></td><td>Creates audit log table if not exists, adds missing columns</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">on-run-end</td><td><code>capture_run_results()</code></td><td>Captures all node results with DML counts to audit table</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">on-run-end</td><td><code>grant_select_for_data_observability()</code></td><td>Grants SELECT permissions for monitoring tools</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3><code>capture_run_results</code> Deep Dive</h3>
    <p>This is the most sophisticated audit macro. For each executed node it:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Extracts timing information (compile start/end, execute start/end)</li>
        <li>Captures Snowflake <code>query_id</code> from the adapter response</li>
        <li>Runs <code>RESULT_SCAN('query_id')</code> to extract DML counts (rows inserted/updated/deleted)</li>
        <li>For table materializations, queries <code>COUNT(*)</code> to get row counts</li>
        <li>Batches inserts (100 rows per batch) to avoid query size limits</li>
        <li>Includes SQL-injection-safe escaping for all string fields</li>
    </ol>

    <h3><code>generate_schema_name</code> Override</h3>
    <p>Overrides dbt's default schema generation to use <strong>custom schema names as-is</strong> (without the target schema prefix). This enables direct routing to schemas like <code>ODS</code>, <code>WORKFORCE</code>, <code>SHARED_DIMS</code>.</p>
</section>

<hr>

<!-- ═══════════════════════ TESTING ═══════════════════════ -->

<section id="testing">
    <h2>🧪 Testing Framework</h2>
    <p>The project features a comprehensive testing strategy with <strong>72+ data tests</strong> across all layers. All tests default to <code>severity: warn</code> (configurable in <code>dbt_project.yml</code>).</p>

    <div class="flow">
        <div class="flow-node node-bronze">Bronze Tests<br><small>~17 per model</small></div>
        <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
        <div class="flow-node node-silver">Silver Tests<br><small>~13 per model</small></div>
        <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
        <div class="flow-node node-gold">Gold Tests<br><small>~19 dim + ~23 fact</small></div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="generic-tests">
    <h2>📐 Generic (Reusable) Tests</h2>
    <p>Located in <code>tests/generic/</code>, these parametric test macros are used across multiple models:</p>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Test</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">check_scd_integrity</td><td>Validates SCD2 tables: no date gaps, IS_CURRENT consistency, EFF_DT &lt; DISC_DT, single active record per key</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">check_is_current_flg</td><td>Verifies IS_CURRENT = TRUE only when DISC_DT = '9999-12-31'</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">check_gaps_in_eff_disc_dt</td><td>Detects gaps between consecutive EFF_DT/DISC_DT ranges</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">check_eff_dt_greater_than_disc_dt</td><td>Ensures effective dates precede discontinuation dates</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">compare_row_counts</td><td>Compares deduped source row count against target count</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">compare_pk_stage_ods</td><td>PK reconciliation between staging and ODS layers</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">check_duplicate_disc_dt_for_unique_key</td><td>Ensures no duplicate open records per key</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">check_model_freshness</td><td>Validates data freshness based on timestamp columns</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">boolean_binary</td><td>Validates columns contain only 0/1 or TRUE/FALSE</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">email_format</td><td>Validates email address format via regex</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">ein_format</td><td>Validates Employee Identification Number format</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">phone_format</td><td>Validates phone number format</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">no_self_supervision</td><td>Ensures employees don't supervise themselves</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">date_not_future</td><td>Ensures date columns aren't in the future</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">positive_values</td><td>Validates numeric columns are positive</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">middle_initial_format</td><td>Validates single-character middle initial</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">check_job_cd_change</td><td>Validates job code change integrity</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</section>

<section id="singular-tests">
    <h2>🎯 Singular Tests by Layer</h2>
    <p>Located in <code>tests/singular/</code>, organized by model name. These are pre-written SQL tests specific to each model.</p>

    <h3>Cross-Layer Reconciliation Pattern</h3>
    <p>Each layer-to-layer transition includes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Row Count Reconciliation:</strong> <code>test_*_row_count</code> — ensures no data loss between layers</li>
        <li><strong>PK Reconciliation:</strong> <code>test_*_pk_reconciliation</code> — verifies all PKs carry through</li>
        <li><strong>Referential Integrity:</strong> <code>test_*_referential_integrity</code> — validates FK relationships</li>
    </ul>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Test Category</th><th>Bronze</th><th>Silver</th><th>Gold Dim</th><th>Gold Fact</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>PK not null / unique</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅ (SK)</td><td>✅</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Audit columns not null</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Email format</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Row count reconciliation</td><td>STG→ODS</td><td>ODS→CDM</td><td>CDM→Core</td><td>DIM→Fact</td></tr>
            <tr><td>PK reconciliation</td><td>STG→ODS</td><td>STG→CDM, ODS→CDM</td><td>CDM→Core</td><td>DIM→Fact</td></tr>
            <tr><td>No self-supervision</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SCD integrity</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>✅</td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>One current per key</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>✅</td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Event type validation</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>✅</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tenure consistency</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>✅</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>LLM-Assisted Test Generation</h3>
    <p>The <code>tests/automation/</code> directory contains an LLM prompt template (<code>LLM_prompt.txt</code>) for generating comprehensive test suites for new models. Feed it the model SQL and YAML to produce a complete test YAML block.</p>
</section>

<hr>

<!-- ═══════════════════════ OPERATIONS ═══════════════════════ -->

<section id="running">
    <h2>🚀 Running the Project</h2>

    <h3>Common Commands</h3>
<pre><code># Build everything (models + tests) for the full lifecycle lineage
dbt build --select +FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE

# Run only models (no tests)
dbt run --select +FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE

# Run only tests
dbt test --select +FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE

# Full refresh (recreate tables from scratch)
dbt build --select +FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE --full-refresh

# Run a specific layer
dbt build --select tag:bronze
dbt build --select tag:silver
dbt build --select tag:gold

# Run a single model and its tests
dbt build --select DIM_EMPLOYEE</code></pre>

    <h3>What Happens During a Build</h3>
    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Phase</th><th>Node Count</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>on-run-start</td><td>1 hook</td><td>Create audit log table</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Bronze</td><td>2 models + ~17 tests</td><td>ODS incremental load with purge/delete hooks</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Silver</td><td>1 model + ~13 tests</td><td>CDM enrichment and transformation</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gold (Dim)</td><td>1 model + ~19 tests</td><td>SCD Type 2 merge</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gold (Fact)</td><td>1 model + ~23 tests</td><td>Full-refresh lifecycle event derivation</td></tr>
            <tr><td>on-run-end</td><td>2 hooks</td><td>Capture run results + grant permissions</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Total: ~6 models + 72 tests + 3 hooks = ~79 nodes per build</strong></p>
</section>

<section id="conventions">
    <h2>📝 Naming Conventions</h2>

    <table class="tbl">
        <thead><tr><th>Element</th><th>Convention</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Bronze Models</td><td><code>ODS_{SOURCE}_{ENTITY}</code></td><td><code>ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Silver Models</td><td><code>{ENTITY}</code> (business name)</td><td><code>EMPLOYEE</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gold Dimensions</td><td><code>DIM_{ENTITY}</code></td><td><code>DIM_EMPLOYEE</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gold Facts</td><td><code>FACT_{ENTITY}_{PROCESS}</code></td><td><code>FACT_EMPLOYEE_LIFECYCLE</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Primary Keys</td><td><code>{LAYER}_{ENTITY}_PK</code></td><td><code>ODS_WORKDAY_EMPLOYEE_PK</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Surrogate Keys</td><td><code>{ENTITY}_SK</code></td><td><code>EMPLOYEE_SK</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Batch IDs</td><td><code>{LAYER}_INS_BATCH_ID</code></td><td><code>ODS_INS_BATCH_ID</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Timestamps</td><td><code>{LAYER}_{ACTION}_TIMESTAMP</code></td><td><code>CDM_UPDATE_TIMESTAMP</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Hash Columns</td><td><code>HASH_CHANGE</code>, <code>HASH_FULL</code></td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SCD Fields</td><td><code>EFF_DT</code>, <code>DISC_DT</code>, <code>IS_CURRENT</code></td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Source YAML</td><td><code>z_{source}_sources.yml</code> (z prefix sorts last)</td><td><code>z_workday_sources.yml</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tests (singular)</td><td><code>test_{model}_{description}</code></td><td><code>test_dim_employee_scd2_no_overlapping_dates</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tags</td><td>Layer + domain + source</td><td><code>["gold","workday","workforce","core-dims"]</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</section>

<section id="adding-model">
    <h2>➕ Adding a New Model (Step-by-Step)</h2>
    <p>Follow this checklist when adding a new entity to the medallion architecture:</p>

    <h3>Step 1: Define Source</h3>
    <div class="card">
        <p>Create <code>models/1_bronze/{source}/z_{source}_sources.yml</code> with source database, schema, and tables.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 2: Bronze (ODS) Model</h3>
    <div class="card">
        <ol>
            <li>Create <code>ODS_{SOURCE}_{ENTITY}.sql</code> with the standard CTE pattern</li>
            <li>Configure: <code>materialized='incremental'</code>, <code>unique_key</code>, <code>merge_condition</code> with hash, pre/post hooks</li>
            <li>Add <code>generate_surrogate_key</code> for PK, <code>generate_hash_change</code> and <code>generate_hash_full</code></li>
            <li>Include audit metadata columns (batch IDs, timestamps, operation type, DQ fields)</li>
            <li>Create YAML with column definitions, marking <code>meta: { natural_key: true }</code> and <code>meta: { audit_column: true }</code></li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 3: Silver (CDM) Model</h3>
    <div class="card">
        <ol>
            <li>Create <code>{ENTITY}.sql</code> referencing Bronze models via <code>{{ ref('ODS_...') }}</code></li>
            <li>Apply business naming, type standardization, and cross-source enrichment</li>
            <li>Configure incremental with hash-based merge condition</li>
            <li>Add hash columns for downstream change detection</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 4: Gold Dimension (SCD Type 2)</h3>
    <div class="card">
        <ol>
            <li>Create <code>DIM_{ENTITY}.sql</code> with <code>materialized='scd_incremental'</code></li>
            <li>Set <code>incremental_strategy='scd+merge'</code> and <code>timestamp_column</code></li>
            <li>Map CDM <code>HASH_FULL</code> to <code>DBT_HASH</code></li>
            <li>Add SCD fields: <code>EFF_DT = CURRENT_DATE</code>, <code>DISC_DT = '9999-12-31'</code>, <code>IS_CURRENT = true</code></li>
            <li>Generate surrogate key from business key + EFF_DT</li>
            <li>Add post-hook for soft-delete propagation if applicable</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 5: Gold Fact (Optional)</h3>
    <div class="card">
        <ol>
            <li>Create <code>FACT_{ENTITY}_{PROCESS}.sql</code> as <code>materialized='table'</code></li>
            <li>Use <code>LAG()</code> window functions over SCD2 versions to detect events</li>
            <li>Derive measures, flags, and fiscal calendar fields</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 6: Tests</h3>
    <div class="card">
        <ol>
            <li>Add generic tests in the model YAML (not_null, unique, accepted_values, relationships)</li>
            <li>Create singular tests in <code>tests/singular/{model_name}/</code></li>
            <li>Include cross-layer reconciliation tests (row counts, PK reconciliation, referential integrity)</li>
            <li>Optionally use the LLM prompt in <code>tests/automation/LLM_prompt.txt</code> to generate a comprehensive test suite</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 7: Update <code>dbt_project.yml</code></h3>
    <div class="card">
        <p>Add database/schema routing under the appropriate layer in the <code>models:</code> config block.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<footer>
    <p>RS Medallion Developer Guide · Built with dbt Core 1.9 + Snowflake · Generated March 2026</p>
    <p>Source: <a href="https://github.com/ananth-gade/RS_Medallion">github.com/ananth-gade/RS_Medallion</a></p>
</footer>

</main>
</div>

<!-- ===== Active nav highlighting ===== -->
<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const links = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-link');
    const sections = [];
    links.forEach(link => {
        const id = link.getAttribute('href')?.replace('#', '');
        if (id) { const el = document.getElementById(id); if (el) sections.push({ el, link }); }
    });
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
        entries.forEach(entry => {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                links.forEach(l => l.classList.remove('active'));
                const match = sections.find(s => s.el === entry.target);
                if (match) match.link.classList.add('active');
            }
        });
    }, { rootMargin: '-80px 0px -60% 0px', threshold: 0 });
    sections.forEach(s => observer.observe(s.el));
});
</script>

</body>
</html>
